<title>USA: NHL ICE HOCKEY-FINALISTS FOR ANNUAL AWARDS FOR 1996-97 SEASON.</title>
<headline>NHL ICE HOCKEY-FINALISTS FOR ANNUAL AWARDS FOR 1996-97 SEASON.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-05-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>The following are the finalists</p>
<p>for the National Hockey League's annual awards for the</p>
<p>1996-1997 season, which were announced by the league on</p>
<p>Thursday.</p>
<p>HART TROPHY (Most Valuable Player)</p>
<p>Mario Lemieux, Pittsburgh Penguins</p>
<p>Dominik Hasek, Buffalo Sabres</p>
<p>Paul Kariya, Mighty Ducks of Anaheim</p>
<p>JAMES NORRIS TROPHY (Top Defenceman)</p>
<p>Brian Leetch, New York Rangers</p>
<p>Vladimir Konstantinov, Detroit Red Wings</p>
<p>Sandis Ozolinsh, Colorado Avalanche</p>
<p>FRANK SELKE TROPHY (Top Defensive Forward)</p>
<p>Peter Forsberg, Colorado Avalanche</p>
<p>Jere Lehtinen, Dallas Stars</p>
<p>Michael Peca, Buffalo Sabres</p>
<p>CALDER TROPHY (Rookie of the Year)</p>
<p>Jim Campbell, St Louis Blues</p>
<p>Jarome Iginla, Calgary Flames</p>
<p>Bryan Berard, New York Islanders</p>
<p>VEZINA TROPHY (Top Goaltender)</p>
<p>Martin Brodeur, New Jersey Devils</p>
<p>Dominik Hasek, Buffalo Sabres</p>
<p>Patrick Roy, Colorado Avalanche</p>
<p>LADY BYNG TROPHY (Sportsmanship and Gentlemanly Conduct)</p>
<p>Paul Kariya, Mighty Ducks of Anaheim</p>
<p>Adam Oates, Washington Capitals</p>
<p>Teemu Selanne, Mighty Ducks of Anaheim</p>
<p>JACK ADAMS AWARD (Coach of the Year)</p>
<p>Ken Hitchcock, Dallas Stars</p>
<p>Jacques Martin, Ottawa Senators</p>
<p>Ted Nolan, Buffalo Sabres</p>
<p>Note: Voting for the awards was conducted at the</p>
<p>conclusion of the regular season. The winners will be</p>
<p>announced at the NHL's annual awards ceremony June 19 in</p>
<p>Toronto.</p>
</text>
